    "form_header_text": "OFFICE OF CONGRESSMEMBER NANETTE DIAZ BARRAG\u00c1N\nCalifornia's 44th Congressional District\n\nFISCAL YEAR 2027 APPROPRIATIONS REQUEST FORM\nFOR PROGAMMATIC FUNDING AND\nREPORT LANGUAGE REQUESTS",
    "form_instructions_text": "Thank you for your interest in submitting appropriations requests through my\nCongressional office. For all requests, please complete the form below and submit it to\nsean.kearns@mail.house.gov no later than March 6, 2026.\n\nMy office will evaluate each request and make a determination on which requests will\nbe submitted to the House Appropriations subcommittees.\n\nThis form is ONLY for programmatic funding and report language requests.\n\nIf you are interested in submitting a Community Project Funding (CPF) request, do not\ncomplete this form. Please contact my office and ask for the CPF Request Form.\n\nAll communication with the office (including meeting requests) for CPF\nrequests must come directly from the entity who would receive the funds being\nrequested and who would directly benefit from the project.\n\nWe do not allow outside consultants or lobbyists to take part in our process - i.e. no\noutreach, meeting requests, submission of documents or projects, or any direct\nengagement to our office for CPF requests, or the projects won't be considered.\nLobbyists and consultants can work directly with the entity to prep any required docs,\nconsult, provide materials, etc.",
