            "field_type": "textarea",
            "required": false,
            "options": null,
            "is_constituent_info": false,
            "is_prior_year_field": false,
            "draft_value": "* NASA's Science Mission Directorate (SMD) manages a portfolio of over 100 missions across Earth Science, Planetary Science, Astrophysics, and Heliophysics.\n* It executes the scientific priorities established by the National Academies' Decadal Surveys, ensuring U.S. global leadership in space discovery.\n* Programs include critical initiatives such as planetary defense, searching for lunar water, and maintaining the aerospace workforce through steady R&D demand.\n* The requested $9 billion restores stability after recent budget disruptions, protecting the specialized talent and infrastructure required for 21st-century exploration.",
            "rationale": "Description based on the provided advocacy talking points and programmatic short title. Highlights the $9B request and core SMD functions.",
